00:00:00.450 --> 00:00:02.270
So we've finally gone through the first step

00:00:02.270 --> 00:00:05.010
of the central dogma, transcription, and we have

00:00:05.010 --> 00:00:07.340
our MRNA. So the second step of the

00:00:07.340 --> 00:00:10.690
central dogma is to turn that MRNA into protein

00:00:10.690 --> 00:00:14.560
using a process called translation. Translation relies heavily

00:00:14.560 --> 00:00:17.410
on the molecular machinery. On a component known

00:00:17.410 --> 00:00:21.230
as a ribosome. Ribosomes are the main driver

00:00:21.230 --> 00:00:25.500
of translation. Ribosomes are actually able to read an

00:00:25.500 --> 00:00:31.850
MRNA sequence by taking it in at one end and reading the MRNA sequence

00:00:31.850 --> 00:00:36.480
all the way through to the other end. And as it does this, it takes those 20

00:00:36.480 --> 00:00:40.740
amino acids And reads the code determining which

00:00:40.740 --> 00:00:45.260
amino acid belongs in a particular position. Now

00:00:45.260 --> 00:00:51.050
one of the most exciting puzzles of the 20th century, was to figure out how this

00:00:51.050 --> 00:00:54.180
code worked? I mean how is that this genetic code

