acid. Was it one base, one letter, per amino

00:01:04.709 --> 00:01:06.730
acid? If true, that would only give us

00:01:06.730 --> 00:01:09.600
four possible combinations: an A, a G, a C,

00:01:09.600 --> 00:01:15.150
or a U, and we know that we have at least 20 amino acids to get to.

00:01:15.150 --> 00:01:17.910
If it's two bases per amino acid Then

